|text1     = The Coreflame Casket is used to contain important items. When activated, {{Color|h|nobold=1|keyholes}} will appear on the exterior of the Coreflame Casket and activate the corresponding number of {{Color|h|nobold=1|key fragments}}.
|image2    = Tutorial Coreflame Casket and Arcane Lock 2.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_322002.png>-<Tutorial Coreflame Casket and Arcane Lock 2.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text2     = Key fragments will continuously {{Color|h|nobold=1|rotate}} at a fixed pace. At the same time, a {{Color|h|nobold=1|projection}} will be generated over the keyhole. Use Oronyx's Prayer to {{Color|h|nobold=1|Rewind the fragments and alter the projection}}.
|image3    = Tutorial Coreflame Casket and Arcane Lock 3.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_322003.png>-<Tutorial Coreflame Casket and Arcane Lock 3.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text3     = If the projection inside the keyhole is {{Color|h|nobold=1|green}}, the {{Color|h|nobold=1|projection is correct}}. The projection outside the keyhole is orange and is considered to be redundant. When the projection and keyhole are {{Color|h|nobold=1|perfectly overlapped}}, the keyhole will be automatically unlocked. When all keyholes have been unlocked, the Coreflame Casket will open.
